<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-11-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="107" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                    <head>No. 820.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Whitehouse</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-11-13"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 13,
                            1888</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 162.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your dispatch No. 178, of the 1st
                        instant, I telegraphed, you on the 10th instant to formally request the
                        extradition of Shields and Wilson.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>